message: Hey team! New workout program update from Advik?
Ah, yes! Advik's sending an update every 2 weeks to track progress.
Hey Rohan! Update attached. Let me know if you have any questions!
Ruby, I'm struggling with ~50% adherence. Any suggestions for small swaps/tweaks?
Ah, Rohan! Try swapping cardio days with strength training or adding more HIIT sessions. Tweaking your nutrition could also help.
Hey team! What's the best approach to fasting vs eating pre-workout? Anyone have insights?
Fasting pre-workout can be tough, but some people swear by it. Try experimenting and see what works for you!
Hi Rohan! Fasting before workout is okay, but eating a balanced meal 1-2 hours prior might give you more energy.
Hey team! Any recommendations for supplements that support brain health?
Actually, Rohan, omega-3 and B vitamins are great for brain health. You can also look into phosphatidylserine.
Sleep debt is real! How do you guys handle it? Do you track HRV too?
Hey Rohan! I use a sleep tracker and prioritize winding down before bed. Tracking HRV helps me optimize my recovery.
Yeah, tracking HRV can be super helpful. It shows when your body needs more rest or recovery.
Sauna or steam room? Which is better for recovery?
Both are great! Sauna's amazing for detox and relaxation, while steam rooms help with flexibility and warmth.
Hey, what's the latest on my workout program? When's the next update?
Hi Rohan! Your 6-week progress report is due in 2 weeks. Keep crushing it!
Rohan just asked about his workout program.
Hey Rohan! You're at 50% adherence. Let's make some small swaps/tweaks to boost that number.
Thanks for the nudge, Ruby. What do you suggest?
How about switching up your warm-up routine or adding some extra reps?
Sounds good! Any thoughts on fasting vs eating pre-workout? Which one gives me more energy?
Rohan wants to know if fasting is better than eating before workout for energy.
Hi Rohan! Fasting can give you a temporary energy boost, but it's not always the best approach. Eating a balanced meal 1-2 hours pre-workout works well for most people.
Got it! What about supplements for brain health? Are there any good ones?
Hey Rohan! Omega-3 and BDNF-supporting supplements can be helpful for brain health. Consult with your doctor before adding anything new!
Thanks, Carla! Any tips on how to tackle sleep debt?
Hi Rohan! Aim for 7-8 hours of sleep each night. Consistency is key.
Hey Advik, how's my new workout program looking? Need any adjustments?
Hey Rohan! Your progress is great! Just need to tweak your warm-up exercises. I'll send you an updated schedule.
Hi Ruby, just got a message from Rohan about his workout. What's the update on his adherence rate?
Hey Sarah! Rohan's at 45% adherence. We should make some small swaps/tweaks to get him closer to 50%. Small wins will add up!

Hey Rohan! Fasting pre-workout can be beneficial for fat-burning, but eating a balanced snack might provide more energy. Try both and see what works best for you!
Got it. What about supplements for brain health? Worth investing in?
Hi Rohan! Some brain-boosting supplements like omega-3s and Ginkgo Biloba can be beneficial. However, always consult with Dr. Warren before adding any new supplements.
Cool. How do I tackle my sleep debt? Been having trouble sleeping lately.
Hey Rohan! Try establishing a consistent bedtime routine and avoiding screens for at least an hour before bed. Also, consider speaking with Dr. Warren about potential sleep-related issues.
Thanks Carla. What's the deal with HRV tracking? Worth monitoring?
Hi Rohan! HRV tracking can be useful for monitoring stress levels and optimizing workouts. I'll send you some recommendations on how to get started.

Hey Rohan! Sauna sessions can help with detoxification and relaxation. Just be sure to stay hydrated afterwards!
